value.raw: ; Define two 5-note scales with different pitches and partial overlap
; Transpose to set the base pitch to the current pitch of `d`, then
; switch to the 5-JI scale for p2.
; Error: can't transpose using unknown notes
; okay -- they both have q and r
; note does not exist in default tuning
; note does not exist in some of the parts
; note does not have the same value in all of the parts
; valid since p is the root in both p1 and p2
; Define two 5-note scales with different pitches and partial overlap

define_scale(scale="5-EDO") <<
  ^0|5 p
  ^1|5 q
  ^2|5 r
  ^3|5 s
  ^4|5 t
>>

define_scale(scale="5-JI") <<
    1 p
  5/4 q
  4/3 r
  3/2 u
  7/4 v
>>
; Transpose to set the base pitch to the current pitch of `d`, then
; switch to the 5-JI scale for p2.
; Error: can't transpose using unknown notes
; okay -- they both have q and r
[p2.0]  1:p q r s ; s is an error
[p3.0]  1:p q r s ; uses global tuning
; note does not exist in default tuning
; note does not exist in some of the parts
; note does not have the same value in all of the parts
; valid since p is the root in both p1 and p2

check_pitch(
    var="x2" ; unknown
    var="x1"
    pitch=440
    pitch=220*2
    part="p4"
    part="p3"
    note="a"
)
